# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 2012-major-league-baseball-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The **1876 major league baseball season** was contested from April 22 through October 21, 1876, and saw the Chicago White Stockings as the pennant winner of the inaugural season of the National League and of Major League baseball.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] Two non-NA teams would join as charter members, including the Cincinnati Reds (unrelated to the modern team) and Louisville Grays.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The 1876 schedule was formatted so that each team would play up to 10 games against each team in the league (split evenly between home and away games), for a maximum of 70 games (only fulfilled by the Boston Red Caps).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] Any game played against a team at home must be played within two months' time away, "under penalty of forfeiture." This was the only season that the National League adopted this format.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The following season would see a more regulated format, requiring teams to schedule 12 games against each team.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] Opening Day took place on April 22 featuring a game between the Boston Red Caps and Athletics of Philadelphia.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The final day of the season was on October 21, featuring a game between the Hartford Dark Blues and Boston Red Caps.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The first doubleheader in major league history occurred on September 9 between the Cincinnati Reds and Hartford Dark Blues.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The year ended with the first postseason competition in major league history.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The contest featured the first and second-place regular season finishers.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] Three tie games, which are not factored into winning percentage or games behind occurred throughout the season (though standings were determined by total wins, not winning percentage).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The Louisville Grays had three tie games.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The Hartford Dark Blues, New York Mutuals, and Philadelphia Athletics had one tie game each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] The Hartford Dark Blues would play their final game at the Hartford Ball Club Grounds on September 16 against the St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1876-major-league-baseball-season] Louis Brown Stockings, relocating to Brooklyn, New York at the Union Grounds as the Brooklyn Hartfords for the start of the 1877 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The **1877 major league baseball season** was contested from April 30 through October 6, 1877, and saw the Boston Red Caps as the pennant winner of the second season of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] Over the off-season, in December 1876, two teams were formally kicked out of the league for failing to fulfill their schedules: New York Mutuals and Philadelphia Athletics, contracting the league from eight to six teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The Hartford Dark Blue would relocate from Hartford, Connecticut to Brooklyn, New York, as the Brooklyn Hartfords.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The 1877 schedule consisted of 60 games for all six teams of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] Each team was scheduled to play 12 games against the other five teams in the league.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] This was the first season that the National League adopted the format.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The format would last only through the following season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] Opening Day took place on April 30 featuring a game between the Boston Red Caps and Brooklyn Hartfords.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The final day of the season was on October 6, featuring four teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The Brooklyn Hartfords hosted a neutral site game.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The Brooklyn Hartfords had two tie games.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The Boston Red Caps, Chicago White Stockings, Cincinnati Reds, and Louisville Grays had one tie game each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The Chicago White Stockings would play their final game at 23rd Street Grounds on October 6 against the Louisville Grays, moving to Lakefront Park for the start of the 1878 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1877-major-league-baseball-season] The Brooklyn Hartfords hosted a neutral site game against the Chicago White Stockings on their last home game of the season, September 22, at the site of the former National Association's New Haven Elm Citys, at the Howard Avenue Grounds in New Haven, Connecticut.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] The **1878 major league baseball season** was contested from May 1 through September 30, 1878, and saw the Boston Red Caps as the pennant winner of the third season of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] Over the off-season, in December 1877, two teams would fold: Brooklyn Hartfords and St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] They were replaced by the Indianapolis Blues and Milwaukee Grays.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] Later in the offseason, the Providence Grays would join on February 6, raising the number of teams to seven.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] On April 1 or 2, the Louisville Grays would officially resign from the league, once again lowering the number of teams to six.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] The 1878 schedule consisted of 60 games for all six teams of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] This format had been in place since the previous season, and would be the final season which saw this format, due to expansion to eight teams the following season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] Opening Day took place on May 1 featuring all six teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] The final day of the season was on September 30, featuring a game between the Boston Red Caps and Providence Grays.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] Two teams hosted games at neutral sites, the Indianapolis Blues and Providence Grays.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] Four tie games, which are not factored into winning percentage or games behind occurred throughout the season (though standings were determined by total wins, not winning percentage).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] The Indianapolis Blues had three tie games.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] The Chicago White Stockings, Cincinnati Reds, and Milwaukee Grays had one tie game each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] Any team shown in small text indicates a previous team a player was on during the season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1878-major-league-baseball-season] The Chicago White Stockings leave the 23rd Street Grounds (where they played for four seasons since their National Association days from 1874) and move to Lakefront Park where they would play for seven seasons through 1884.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The **1879 major league baseball season** was contested from May 1 through September 30, 1879, and saw the Providence Grays as the pennant winner of the fourth season of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] Over the off-season, the National League was set on expanding from a six-team league to an eight-team league.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The Indianapolis Blues and Milwaukee Grays folded, and in its place, the league admitted the Cleveland Blues, the International Association's Buffalo Bisons and Syracuse Stars, and finally (with confirmation Milwaukee was not returning) the Troy Trojans.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] It is suggested by Society for American Baseball Research (SABR) that this season featured the first African-American to play major league baseball, William Edward White, who played one game with the Providence Grays on June 21.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] He predates brothers Moses Fleetwood Walker and Weldy Walker by five years, and Jackie Robinson by 68 years.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The 1879 schedule consisted of 84 games for all eight teams of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] Each team was scheduled to play 12 games against the other seven teams in the league.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] This format was an adjustment to the 12-games-each format that had been in place since 1877, as the National League expanded from six to eight teams, adding 24 games to each team's schedule.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] Opening Day took place on May 1 featuring all eight teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The final day of the season was on September 30, featuring six teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] Five tie games, which are not factored into winning percentage or games behind occurred throughout the season (though standings were determined by total wins, not winning percentage).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The Chicago White Stockings had four tie games.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The Buffalo Bisons, Cincinnati Reds, Providence Grays, and Syracuse Stars had one tie game each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1879-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans would play their final game at the Putnam Grounds on September 20 against the Chicago White Stockings, moving to Haymakers' Grounds for the start of the 1880 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The **1880 major league baseball season** was contested from May 1 through October 1, 1880, and saw the Chicago White Stockings as the pennant winner of the fifth season of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The 1880 season is known for the first two major league perfect games in history, as well as being the only perfect games in the 19th century.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] Thrown by Lee Richmond and John Ward, these two perfect games were thrown in the span of five days, the shortest amount of time between two perfect games (the next closest is currently 20 days between Dallas Braden's May 9 and Roy Halladay's and May 29, 2010 perfect games).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] A perfect game would not be seen again in the Major Leagues for 24 years when Cy Young threw his perfect game in 1904.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] Over the off-season, the Cincinnati Reds and Syracuse Stars disbanded, and were replaced by the Cincinnati Stars and Worcester Worcesters.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] This would be the Stars' only major league season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The 1880 schedule consisted of 84 games for all eight teams of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] This continued the format put in place since the previous season and would be used until 1883.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The final day of the season was on October 1, featuring a doubleheader between the Providence Grays and Worcester Worcesters.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] Eight tie games, which are not factored into winning percentage or games behind occurred throughout the season (though standings were determined by total wins, not winning percentage).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The Buffalo Bisons, Cincinnati Stars, and Providence Grays had three tie games each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The Boston Red Caps, Chicago White Stockings, and Worcester Worcesters had two tie games each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans leave the Putnam Grounds (where they played their inaugural seasons) and move to the Haymakers' Grounds, where they would play for two seasons through 1881.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1880-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans begin to host a few games at Riverside Park in nearby Greenbush, New York, playing on September 11.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The **1881 major league baseball season** was contested from April 30 through September 30, 1881, and saw the Chicago White Stockings as the pennant winner of the sixth season of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The 1881 season is most known for featuring the first major league grand slam.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] Roger Connor of the Troy Trojans hit the walk-off home run at Riverside Park (Greenbush) against the Worcester Worcesters on September 10, leading to an 8–7 victory.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] Over the off-season, the National League dropped the Cincinnati Stars because the team refused to sign a league pledge that banned alcohol in league parks and forbade clubs from renting their parks out on Sundays.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The team was replaced by the Detroit Wolverines.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] 1881 would be the final season of the first National League monopoly-era, as the American Association would be established in 1882.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The 1881 schedule consisted of 84 games for all eight teams of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] This continued the format put in place since 1879 and would be used until 1883.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] Opening Day took place on April 30 featuring four teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The final day of the season was on September 30, featuring all eight teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] Two tie games, which are not factored into winning percentage or games behind occurred throughout the season (though standings were determined by total wins, not winning percentage).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The Cleveland Blues, Providence Grays, Troy Trojans, and Worcester Worcesters had one tie game each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The Detroit Wolverines join the National League and play at Recreation Park in Detroit, Michigan.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans would play their final game at Haymakers' Grounds on September 30 against the Detroit Wolverines, moving to the Troy Ball Clubs Grounds for the start of the 1882 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1881-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans continue to host a few games at Riverside Park in nearby Greenbush, New York, playing on June 15 and September 10.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The **1882 major league baseball season** was contested from May 1 through October 2, 1882.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] It was the inaugural season for the American Association (AA) and seventh season for the National League (NL).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The Cincinnati Red Stockings won the AA pennant, while the Chicago White Stockings won the NL pennant.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The American Association was established as a six-team league in cities not represented by the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The AA was established with the expectation that it would have more of a "liberal policy" and better labor relations, threatening the puritanical NL, which itself had formal behavior codes with associated policies and procedures and a blacklist for players who did not comply to said rules.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The AA also refused to recognize the NL's reserve lists.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] Three of the six teams of the American Association survive to this day as National League teams; the Cincinnati Red Stockings, Pittsburgh Alleghenys, and St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] Louis Brown Stockings are today's Cincinnati Reds, Pittsburgh Pirates, and St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The 1882 season was the last for the Troy Trojans and Worcester Worcesters.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The 1882 schedule consisted of 80 games for all teams in the six-team American Association, and 84 games for all teams in the eight-team National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] Each American Association team was scheduled to play 16 games against the other five teams, while each National League was scheduled to play 12 games against the other seven teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The 80-game format was unique to the American Association's 1882 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] Meanwhile, the National League had been playing their 84-game schedule, since 1879, though 1882 would be their last.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The following season would see both leagues take on a 98-game format, playing 14 games each against their seven opponents.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] National League Opening Day took place on May 1 featuring all eight teams, while American Association Opening Day took place on May 2, featuring all six teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The National League would see its final day of the regular season on October 2 featuring a game between the Boston Red Caps and Providence Grays, while the American Association would see its final day of the regular season on October 1, featuring a game between the Louisville Eclipse and St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] 5 tie games (1 in AA, 4 in NL), which are not factored into winning percentage or games behind (and were often replayed again) occurred throughout the season (though in the National League, standings were determined by total wins, not winning percentage).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The Baltimore Orioles and Pittsburgh Alleghenys had one tie game each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The Detroit Wolverines had three tie games.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The Cleveland Blues and Troy Trojans had two tie games each.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans leave Haymakers' Grounds (where they played for two seasons) and move to the Troy Ball Clubs Grounds, where they would play until they folded at the end of the season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The Troy Trojans continue to host a few games at Riverside Park in nearby Greenbush, New York, playing their first three home games of the season, May 16–18, as well as a fourth game on game 1 of a doubleheader May 30 at the park.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/1882-major-league-baseball-season] The 1882 season saw three teams play their final games at respective ballparks, before moving to new ballparks for the 1883 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The **2012 Major League Baseball season** began on April 5, 2012 because during the MLB Spring Training it was the first of a two-game series between the Seattle Mariners and the Oakland Athletics at the Tokyo Dome in Japan.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On November 22, 2011, a new contract between Major League Baseball and its players union was ratified, and as a result, an expanded playoff format adding two clubs would be adopted no later than 2013 according to the new Collective Bargaining Agreement.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The new format of the 2012 postseason used the 1 game series of the Wild Card round of the format for the 2012 postseason only.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The restriction against divisional rivals playing against each other in the Division Series round that had existed in previous years was eliminated, as the Baltimore Orioles and New York Yankees squared off in one of the best-of-five LDS in the American League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On April 4, 2012, it was the last day of the MLB Spring Training and ended with the new Marlins Park, as the newly renamed Miami Marlins hosted the defending World Series champion St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The regular season ended on Wednesday, October 3, 2012.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The entire master schedule was released on September 14, 2011.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Major League Baseball postseason was expanded to include a second wild card team in each league beginning in the 2012 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The season marked the last for the Houston Astros as a member of the National League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Following the sale to new owner Jim Crane, the Astros agreed to move to the American League effective in the 2013 season, and would be assigned to the American League West, joining their in-state rivals, the Texas Rangers.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Major League Baseball All-Star Game's 83rd edition was held on July 10, 2012 at Kauffman Stadium in Kansas City, Missouri, with the National League winning the All-Star Game for the third consecutive year in an 8–0 shutout of the American League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] With the win, the National League champion earned home field advantage for the World Series, which began on October 24, 2012 and ended on October 28, 2012 when the San Francisco Giants swept the Detroit Tigers.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Civil Rights Game was held on August 18, 2012 at Turner Field, as the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the host Atlanta Braves, 6–2.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The following managers were hired for the 2012 season after the former manager retired from baseball.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] At the end of the 2011 season, the following teams made replacements to their managers.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Five teams have made wholesale changes to their uniforms in 2012, while a sixth has new road uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Two other teams added alternate uniforms to their existing set.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The San Diego Padres were the first team to announce changes to their logos and uniform set on November 9.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The new primary features the "SD" cap logo inside a navy circle with the words "San Diego Padres Baseball Club" encircling it.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The "swinging friar" logo was also revived, albeit in the current colors.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Another secondary logo features the Padres script from last season below the depiction of Petco Park in sand and above the year of establishment; a blue and white version is used on the away and alternate uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The front of the home uniform remains the same, except that the sand trim in "Padres" is now in trim instead of a drop shadow and the addition of navy piping.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Originally they'll use the sand Petco patch on the left sleeve, but upon unveiling the uniforms, the "swinging friar" patch was placed instead.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The road uniforms now feature "San Diego" in an arched position with navy piping.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The alternate blue uniforms feature the "SD" cap logo on the left chest with white piping.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] All three uniforms now feature the block numerals on the reverse side.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The digital camouflage uniforms were retained, save for the change to block numerals.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The caps with the sand "SD" were retired.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Marlins unveiled their changes on November 11, 2011, as the team was rebranded as the Miami Marlins, complete with a new logo featuring a stylized Marlin jumping over an art deco colored "M" in coral, yellow and blue.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] "MIAMI" will grace the primary white uniform, and there will be an orange home alternate which feature the team name, while the black alt had been reduced to road alternate jersey.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The black cap is used for the regular home, away and black alternates, while the orange cap is paired with the orange alternates.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Marlins become the second team to use the city (or state) name on the home uniforms, after the Texas Rangers.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] November 15 saw the Baltimore Orioles redesign their road and home uniform sets and returned to a version of the cartoon logo used from the mid-1960s to 1988.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The home caps are white in front and black on the back with an orange bill, while the away caps will be all black with an orange bill, both featuring the cartoon bird.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They also unveiled a modernized version of the orange alternate uniforms last worn in 1992, and were worn on select home games, but retained the black alternate uniforms paired with the black and orange cap with the "O's" script.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of their golden anniversary season, the New York Mets modified their home and road uniforms to resemble the style worn in 1962, having their unveiling November 16.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, the black alternate jersey (which will be worn occasionally on the road in 2012) is being phased out, to be replaced by a blue alternate starting in 2013.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The solid black cap with the blue/white/orange crest will also be retained for one more season, to be worn only with the black alternate jersey.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The black cap with blue bill and blue/orange crest has been eliminated.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, the Mets have removed the color black from their batting-practice jerseys and caps; both will be blue with orange lettering/logos outlined in white.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Toronto Blue Jays unveiled new uniforms on November 18, returning to a variation of their vintage logo used from 1977 through 1996.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The new logo is similar to the original used from 1977–96, with a few exceptions: a more prominent maple leaf, a sleeker-looking blue jay, serifed modern lettering on the team name, and a split-line blue circle enclosing the logo.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The new uniforms are similarly based on the set used from 1989–96; a white home uniform with "Blue Jays", a grey road uniform with "Toronto", and a blue alternate uniform with "Blue Jays".
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The team/city name is arched above the secondary logo of the blue jay with the maple leaf, sans the baseball, situated on the left side.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The secondary logo is also placed in the blue cap.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The uniforms use the breathable double-knit polyester fabric, claiming the previously lighter Climate Base fabric became too heavy, once players began to sweat.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Colorado Rockies replaced their purple road pinstripes with a more traditional solid gray uniform which was unveiled at RockiesFest in Denver in January 2012.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The San Francisco Giants and Atlanta Braves added alternate uniforms to their set.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Giants wear a Sunday road game grey alternate based on the road uniforms they wore during their 1989 World Series run, with the interlocking 'SF' logo on the left chest and black neck-hoop piping.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The black piping was also incorporated into the team's normal road gray uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Braves unveiled a cream (heritage white) home alternates based on the uniforms worn in their first season in Atlanta.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The uniform has the 'Braves' wordmark without the tomahawk with the uniform number below on the left chest and navy piping.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The sleeves have a logo commemorating the Braves franchise's first season in 1876.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] A new, slightly altered Los Angeles Dodgers logo made its way to the Dodgers dugout wall at Dodger Stadium and for their "Social September" promotion in September 2011.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The baseball and flight lines have been thickened, while the "o" in the script "Dodgers" no longer has a line on the bottom left.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The home uniform script continues to use the previous script, though.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] After reviving the Northwest Green jerseys at home, the Seattle Mariners brought back their navy with teal bill caps, last worn in 2002, for Monday and Friday home contests.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Also, their navy road alternate will now have "SEATTLE" on the jersey front.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Royals unveiled minor tweaks to their light blue home alternate jersey, with all numbers and lettering now white with royal trim, and a revamped away uniform (changed to a darker blue-gray color and a revamped "Kansas City" script).
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, the team has dropped their light blue caps.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cleveland Indians made minor tweaks to the home and alternate uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The white home uniform features navy collar piping and the 'Indians' script in red and navy trim, removing the white inner trim as well as the navy piping on the button lines.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The navy alternate features gray collar piping and the 'Indians' script in red and white trim, removing the navy inner trim as well as the grey piping on the button lines.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim revert to the silver halo after changing it to gold the previous year.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They also added a sleeve patch that says 'Angels Baseball' with the foundation year (1961) separated by the current logo in between.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The logo is wrapped in a red, navy and silver circle.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This patch will be placed on all uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of their 40th anniversary in Arlington, the Texas Rangers will wear replicas of the four different uniforms they have worn throughout the team's history, the most notable of which are the two uniforms worn during the ownership of then-future president of the United States George W.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of their 50th anniversary, the Astros will wear throwbacks throughout the season, including a game with Colt .45s uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Red Sox and the Yankees wore 1912 throwbacks on April 20 to mark the 100th anniversary of Fenway Park.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] It marked only the second time the Yankees have worn throwbacks; the first was in 1996, when they wore New York Black Yankees uniforms at a Negro leagues tribute game in Detroit.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Red Sox and Athletics wore 1936 uniforms on May 2 at Fenway Park.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Twins wore Minneapolis Millers uniforms on June 30 in the second game of a make-up doubleheader against the Royals, who wore the uniforms of the Kansas City Blues.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Nationals wore the uniforms of the 1924 Washington Senators on July 5 against the Giants, who wore the 1924 New York Giants uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Athletics wore the PCL Oakland Oaks uniforms, and the Mariners the Rainiers, on July 8.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Brewers will wear Milwaukee Bears Negro leagues uniforms on July 28.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Diamondbacks will wear a throwback uniform on September 15.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fans decided online that their 1998 purple uniform will be worn.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The White Sox are wearing 1972 uniforms on Sundays at home this season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Detroit Tigers and Pittsburgh Pirates wore throwback uniforms paying tribute to the Negro league baseball teams Detroit Stars and Pittsburgh Crawfords on May 19.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim and Seattle Mariners wore throwback uniforms of defunct Pacific Coast League teams Los Angeles Angels and Seattle Rainiers on May 26.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago Cubs and San Francisco Giants wore 1912 throwback uniforms on June 2.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Pirates and Royals wore Negro leagues uniforms on June 9 – the Pirates, the Homestead Grays and the Royals, the Kansas City Monarchs.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Tampa Bay Rays wore 'faux-back' 1979 throwback jerseys on June 30 against the Tigers, who also wore throwback jerseys from the same year.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Due to the fact the Rays did not exist as a franchise in 1979, their uniform design was inspired from popular uniform styles such as pullovers and two-tone caps.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The San Diego Padres and New York Mets wore 1989 throwback uniforms on August 3.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Louis Cardinals and Milwaukee Brewers celebrated the 30th anniversary of the 1982 World Series by wearing throwback uniforms on August 4.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cardinals also added a 30th anniversary patch commemorating their World Series victory, exclusive to their throwback uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The next night, the Cardinals wore their road blue uniforms against the Brewers.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cincinnati Reds and Philadelphia Phillies wore throwback uniforms from the 1991 season on August 22.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Ironically, on June 16, 1991, the Reds and Phillies had worn 1957 uniforms at Veterans Stadium.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cardinals wore special uniforms to commemorate their 2011 World Series win on April 13–14.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The 'STL' on the caps was gold with navy trim, while the word 'Cardinals' and the block numbers on the uniforms were gold with navy trim.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cardinals wore them during the unfurling of their championship flag on April 13, and the presentation of the Commissioner's Trophy and World Series rings on April 14.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] 42 on April 15, the 65th anniversary of Jackie Robinson's MLB debut.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Dodgers wore a Brooklyn-era cap and batting helmet that day, as well.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Pirates and Orioles donned camouflage uniforms during Memorial Day weekend.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Brewers wore an Italian-language batting practice uniform with the word "Birrai" on July 1; their opponents Arizona Diamondbacks ('I D-Backs') also wore Italian-language uniforms.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They also wore the Cerveceros uniforms on June 2 against the Pirates ('Piratas').
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Players wore special caps on Memorial Day and Independence Day; the Blue Jays also wore special caps on Canada Day, along with a specialized red uniform.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This year, a camouflage design was used in lieu of the American and Canadian flags.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In commemoration of the September 11 attacks, all American teams wore caps with the American flag sewn on the left; the Blue Jays sported both the American and Canadian flags on both sides of their caps.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of Cinco de Mayo the San Francisco Giants ("Gigantes") and Houston Astros ("Los Astros") wore Spanish-language home uniforms for the game.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] On July 6, the New York Mets ("Los Mets") wore blue Spanish-language jerseys for the game against the Chicago Cubs.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They wore the uniforms again on August 24 against the Astros.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago White Sox wore a variation of their home uniforms on September 7 against the Royals, as part of the "Halfway to St.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The uniform substitutes the traditional black color for green.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Athletics and Diamondbacks wore Spanish-language uniforms in celebration of Mexican Independence Day on September 16, against the Orioles and Giants, respectively.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The A's used their primary home uniform, with "Atléticos" substituting for "Athletics", while the D-Backs used their black alternate uniform, with "Los D-Backs" substituting for the secondary "A" logo.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Florida Marlins vacated Sun Life Stadium at the end of the 2011 season and moved into Marlins Park, which was built on the site of the old Orange Bowl stadium.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The team officially adopted its new name of Miami Marlins on November 11, 2011.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The 2012 season marked the 100th anniversary of the opening of Boston's Fenway Park.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, Dodger Stadium—home of the Los Angeles Dodgers—celebrated its 50th anniversary, and the Baltimore Orioles home, Oriole Park at Camden Yards, also celebrated its 20th anniversary.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The 2012 season also marked the 50th anniversary for the New York Mets and the Houston Astros, but the 51st season for both teams.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Mets began play four years after the Brooklyn Dodgers and New York Giants moved west in 1958, leaving New York City with only one MLB team in the Yankees.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In 1959, New York City attorney William Shea, with support from baseball figures including former Dodgers executive Branch Rickey, proposed a third major league called the Continental League.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Houston and New York City were both among the announced CL cities.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] MLB responded to the threat by placing new franchises in several of these cities, and offered a National League franchise to the owners of the proposed New York CL team, who accepted.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] With Shea's goal of bringing a second major-league team to New York successful, he abandoned the new league, which officially folded in 1960 without ever playing a game.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Mets began play in 1962 at the Giants' former home of the Polo Grounds in Manhattan, moved in 1964 to Shea Stadium (named after the aforementioned William Shea) in Queens, and opened their current home of Citi Field, adjacent to the former Shea Stadium site, in 2009.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Astros were also enfranchised as a direct response to the plans to launch the CL.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They began play in 1962 as the Houston Colt .45s; following a dispute with Colt Firearms over revenues from souvenir sales and licensing fees, the team moved to the Astrodome in 1965 and renamed itself the Astros.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In 2000, they opened their current home, now known as Minute Maid Park.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In honor of the Astros' 50th anniversary, they donned different throwback uniforms at home on Friday night themed to each decade.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Major League Baseball enters the 6th year of seven-year contracts it signed with its broadcast partners prior to the 2007 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This year, Fox will televise the Saturday Game of the Week (which will be shown in prime time each week from May 19 to July 7), the All-Star Game, the National League Championship Series, and the World Series.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TBS will show a Sunday Game of the Week, the All-Star Selection Show, all but two Division Series games, the American League Championship Series, and the new wild card elimination games.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They will also air 10 spring training games, as well as five nationally televised games on Opening Week from April 4–6.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The MLB Network will air a national Game of the Week broadcast every Thursday and the two Division Series games not shown on TBS.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Major League Baseball International will air in syndication the All-Star Game, the ALCS, and the World Series to global markets.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Padres switched from Cox Cable-owned 4SD to a new channel called Fox Sports San Diego, which the Padres also have a minority stake in.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This is the last season of Houston Astros games on Fox Sports Houston and KTXH.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Starting next season, all games will be on Comcast SportsNet Houston, a new channel the Astros will co-own with the Houston Rockets.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Mid-Atlantic Sports Network (MASN), which broadcasts Orioles and Nationals games, became the latest network to adjust its score box to the 16:9 aspect ratio for high-definition television broadcasts.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The adjustment, which began with Fox Sports' MLB coverage in 2010, was later adopted to other networks, notably ESPN, TBS, Fox Sports Net (except Fox Sports South and some terrestrial television broadcasts produced by Fox Sports), and Root Sports during the 2011 season.
[src:2012-major-league-baseball-season/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As of this season, only the YES Network, New England Sports Network, Comcast SportsNet, SportsNet New York and SportsTime Ohio have yet to move to the newly adjusted high definition broadcast.
